    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>The illness of a relation brought me to <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0699">London</placeName> for a few days. I have seen <persName ref="pe0019">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Menzies</persName>
                    &amp; shall again too morrow. The next day I set out for <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0001">home</placeName> &amp; on the 18<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> shall proceed on my way north. I have no one trouble more to give,
                    only to hope that I shall hear from you at <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0253">Carlisle</placeName>:</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>in the Interim am with best complim<hi rend="superscript">ts</hi> to
                        all <lb/>friends Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> obliged &amp;
                        <lb/>most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Th. Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <dateline>May 2<hi rend="superscript">d.</hi> 1772</dateline>

                <postscript>
                    <p>I found both y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Letters here.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <handShift/>
                    <unclear reason="illegible">6</unclear>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <unclear reason="illegible">1:3</unclear>
                </p>
